  <br>
  <h4>Mood</h4>
  <p>
    Moods are color themes that relate to the common Bootstrap naming of 'primary', 'secondary', 'success', 'warning', and 'danger'. You can actually put any string you like and it will add a class {{ui-label 'mood-[name]'}}. For the Bootstrap standard ones there is built-in styling but you can feel free to override or just use a different name.
  </p>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-6 col-md-4">
      {{select-input placeholder='info' mood='info' options=things optgroups=optGroup}}
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-6 col-md-8">
      <pre><code>\{{select-input mood='info'}}</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-6 col-md-4">
